    <abstract id="aspace_c91b96b4167c0406cdc17d667bc92e95">Sanford Jay Rosen is a founding and senior partner at Rosen Bien Galvan &amp; Grunfeld LLP in San Francisco, California, where he concentrates his practice on constitutional and civil rights law, employment law, consumer law, complex commercial litigation, and litigation involving attorneys. He was working for the American Civil Liberties Union during the time he was Alger Hiss' attorney in the 1972 <emph render="italic">Hiss et al. v. Hampton et al.</emph> case. The plaintiffs' annuity applications were denied due to certain provisions of the "Hiss Act." Rosen's papers relate to his time as Alger Hiss' lawyer during this 1972 case to restore his federal pension. Materials include drafts and research for memos, correspondence, and legal research, as well as files related to Alger Hiss' friendship with Mr. Rosen.</abstract>
    <physloc id="aspace_1843faf041d0c622240b1eeff38d9cfe">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
