  <bioghist id="aspace_9775606602688b329ae7348363e89434">
    <head>Biographical Note</head>
<p>Sanford Jay Rosen is a founding and senior partner at Rosen Bien Galvan &amp; Grunfeld LLP in San Francisco, California, where he concentrates his practice on constitutional and civil rights law, employment law, consumer law, complex commercial litigation, and litigation involving attorneys. He was working for the American Civil Liberties Union during the time he was Alger Hiss' attorney in the 1972 <emph render="italic">Hiss et al. v. Hampton et al.</emph> case.</p>  </bioghist>
