  <scopecontent id="aspace_0468835b54ef7c2d0c3229287585f91c">
    <head>Content Description</head>
<p>Sanford Jay Rosen's papers relate to his time as Alger Hiss' lawyer during a case to restore his federal pension. Materials include drafts and research for memos, correspondence, and legal research from the <emph render="italic">Hiss et al. v. Hampton et al.</emph> case, as well as files related to Alger Hiss' friendship with Mr. Rosen.  </p><p>Former employees of the federal government, plaintiffs in the <emph render="italic">Hiss v. Hampton</emph> case had applied for annuities under the Civil Service Retirement Act. Their applications were denied by the Civil Service Commission due to certain provisions of the "Hiss Act." In the <emph render="italic">Hiss v. Hampton</emph> case, Sanford J. Rosen won a dispositive summary judgment motion that declared the Hiss Act an unconstitutional ex post facto law. </p>  </scopecontent>
